From cou.: 6 The SBA-15 support has been optimized by QM calculations without any symmetry constraints. Fig. 1(a) shows the optimized geometry of the SBA-15 model used for calculations. In order to graft the metal complex on the SBA-15 support, the VO4 moiety was placed near the edges and in the centre of SBA-15. The computations on SBA-15 supported VO4 have been performed using a QM/MM scheme with the help of ONIOM. It is a hybrid method that enables different ab initio or semi-empirical methods to be applied to different parts of a molecule/system and has been shown to be a very effective method in heterogeneous catalysis.60–62 Since, the metal cluster is now grafted on an SBA-15 support, the reaction system has been divided into two parts; the bulky SBA-15 part was treated according to MM, while the chemically important region, i.e. the CH3-S-Ph and VO4 embedded SBA-15 site, was subjected to QM calculations (Fig. 1(b)) (the QM level of theory was the same as that applied to the reaction in the gas phase). Full QM calculations have also been performed to obtain the single point energy (SPE) of the SBA-15 supported cluster using the B3LYP-D3 functional.
From Soup: 6 The SBA-15 support has been optimized by QM calculations without any symmetry constraints. Fig. 1(a) shows the optimized geometry of the SBA-15 model used for calculations. In order to graft the metal complex on the SBA-15 support, the VO 4 moiety was placed near the edges and in the centre of SBA-15. The computations on SBA-15 supported VO 4 have been performed using a QM/MM scheme with the help of ONIOM. It is a hybrid method that enables different ab initio or semi-empirical methods to be applied to different parts of a molecule/system and has been shown to be a very effective method in heterogeneous catalysis. 60–62 Since, the metal cluster is now grafted on an SBA-15 support, the reaction system has been divided into two parts; the bulky SBA-15 part was treated according to MM, while the chemically important region, i.e. the CH 3 -S-Ph and VO 4 embedded SBA-15 site, was subjected to QM calculations ( Fig. 1(b) ) (the QM level of theory was the same as that applied to the reaction in the gas phase). Full QM calculations have also been performed to obtain the single point energy (SPE) of the SBA-15 supported cluster using the B3LYP-D3 functional.
