From cou.: 13 The stable VO4 moiety embedded in the centre of the SBA-15 support was selected to carry out sulfoxidation of CH3-S-Ph. Structure analysis of VO4-SBA-15 shows that chirality has been successfully introduced at the vanadium centre. Vanadium is coordinated with four oxygens with different environments (Fig. 8). Two enantiomers (R and S) of VO4-SBA-15 labelled as RVO4-SBA-15 and SVO4-SBA-15 have been optimized using an ONIOM approach. Fig. 8 shows the geometries of two enantiomers of VO4-SBA-15; one with vanadium in an S configuration (SVO4-SBA-15 Fig. 8(a)) and another with vanadium in an R configuration (RVO4-SBA-15 Fig. 8(b)). The reactions of both enantiomers with CH3-S-Ph were studied separately.
From Soup: 13 The stable VO 4 moiety embedded in the centre of the SBA-15 support was selected to carry out sulfoxidation of CH 3 -S-Ph. Structure analysis of VO 4 -SBA-15 shows that chirality has been successfully introduced at the vanadium centre. Vanadium is coordinated with four oxygens with different environments ( Fig. 8 ). Two enantiomers ( R and S ) of VO 4 -SBA-15 labelled as R VO 4 -SBA-15 and S VO 4 -SBA-15 have been optimized using an ONIOM approach. Fig. 8 shows the geometries of two enantiomers of VO 4 -SBA-15; one with vanadium in an S configuration ( S VO 4 -SBA-15 Fig. 8(a) ) and another with vanadium in an R configuration ( R VO 4 -SBA-15 Fig. 8(b) ). The reactions of both enantiomers with CH 3 -S-Ph were studied separately.
